---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Terms and Variables" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-7/" backLabel="← Grade 7">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Terms and Variables</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Learn to calculate with letters</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Why letters in mathematics?</h2>
		<p>Variables are placeholders for numbers. Instead of "a number plus 3" we write <strong>x + 3</strong>. It's shorter and lets us write general rules.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Evaluating Terms</h3>
		<p>The term 2x + 1 gives a different value for each x. Change x and see the result:</p>
	</section>

	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fnExpr="2*x + 1" fnLabel="f(x) = 2x + 1" />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Simplifying Terms</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Combining:</strong> 3x + 2x = 5x (add like terms)</li>
			<li><strong>Expanding:</strong> 2·(x + 3) = 2x + 6</li>
			<li><strong>Factoring:</strong> 6x + 9 = 3·(2x + 3)</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Remember: You can only combine <strong>like</strong> terms! 3x + 2y stays 3x + 2y.</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
